France midfielder Paul Pogba removed beer bottles of headline Euro 2020 sponsor, Heineken, from the table before the start of his post-match press conference with the media. Pogba, who was named Star of the Match, is a devoted Muslim and does not drink alcohol. The Manchester United star took the same route as Cristiano Ronaldo, who also removed Coca-Cola bottles from the table. First Ronaldo with the Coca-Cola...Now Paul Pogba wasn't happy with the Heineken in front of him at his press conference ??? pic.twitter.com/SU1ifQPGOP  Cristiano Ronaldo simply moving Coca Cola out of the way and saying “drink water” caused Coca Cola to lose $4 billion in value today… pic.twitter.com/pOsOsXiXGy 